anyone had a few pointers.<br><br>Thanks in advance.<br><br> <p>Craq 40 Paladin <br>Squire in Emerald Phoenix</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~pfichera/_images/TO.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 804<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/01 7:02:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~pfichera/_images/output1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Ro Armor is not realistically soloable at the level that it is usefull to have it at. Sad but true.<br><br>Get a group of Paladins together and help each other out. That is what I am my Paladin friends did and it worked great for us. <p><I><B>Gilfalas Elaandrin</I></B><br>Guildmaster of Twilight Order<br>Koada'Vie, Defender of Felwithe and Knight of Truth<br>Cavalier of the 52nd<br>Bertoxxulous Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucraq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Craq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/01 1:45:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Thanks for a nice short reply. <p>Craq 40th Paladin <br>Squire in Emerald Phoenix <br>Server : Luclin </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaldaasdei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldaas DeI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/01 4:15:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaldaasdei.tripod.com/Kaldaas45.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> To try and solo the quests at the most beneficial level is really, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> really</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> hard. Myself, I just zoned into Sol A and shouted, wondering if anyone had any spare melatite. I didn't have to pay more than 10pp a bar.<br><br>The specific mobs are a pain to solo, and you must have a good amount of time avail to you. A good single group 30+ that knows what they're doing should be able to take down most of the mobs that are needed though. <p>Kaldaas<br>46th Paladin<br>Divide et Impera<br>Bristlebane Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Summoneaa Saindiva</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/01 6:44:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reply</span><hr size=1> this is realy depressing, I'm just beginning the quest, got 16 faeriers dusts, &amp; 2 MM granites practically &quot;begging&quot; for some1 to help me loot them in MM, I still need 2 granites for the pieces I need, &amp; thinking of how hard it will be to get the melatite I'm thinking of giving up, &amp; just level up a bit in MM which seems to be a nice XP pool for a 33ish..<br>Gargoyles... Why on earth did they have to put the oners with the granites INSIDE the castle, I could easily pull one of the yard's &amp; solo it at the zone..<br>All my friends are afraid of coming to MM, my guild helped me once &amp; it turned into a slaughter once the shamy (healer) died, which makes me think twice b4 asking them for help again, now I sit all night at the MM zone waiting for someone to PLEASE come help me get the granites... The zone is practically empty all day long &amp; trying to venture inside is a suicide....<br>Even when I asked 2 40+ to help me loot it XP neglected, my invis weared off just b4 the gargs, vamps &amp; musicians, which turned into a complete mess when the 3 of us died, I had to pay for their rez as well as mine as a consolation........... Sigh..<br>Now all I'm planing to do when I recover my body 2day is to shout :&quot;L33 pally LFG&quot; PERIOD.. Maybe someday I'll get inside &amp; get my 2 granites... (I dont wanna get back here later for more colection)<br><br>Summoneaa Saindiva<br>Paladin of the 33rd Hand<br>Wildrunners <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaldaasdei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaldaas DeI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/1/01 7:44:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://kaldaasdei.tripod.com/Kaldaas.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Mistmoore sucks. Period. I don't remember having that much trouble though. One (if you're good)/Two groups 35+ can storm through the entrance in the pit and get some granite, or take the two gargoyle spawns in the pit itself with Enyti.  <p>Kaldaas<br>47th Paladin<br>Divide et Impera<br>Bristlebane Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugarthintrueknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garthin Trueknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/01 7:53:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> To the pally who wanted to know about mm granite. THE best place, and safest place, to farm mm granite, is in the hallway between the &quot;torture&quot; room and the pool. You invis to cy. KEY POINT: Wait untill the day spawn comes online. Several of mm night mobs see thru invis. Next go behind the crypt to secret wall, DO not stop in jail, casters will hit u but unless you open jail doors they can't chase you. Go to top of stairs, there's a &quot;T&quot; intersection. Go left and enter the torture room, clear spawn. Go to next room, 2 gargs there. They drop garnite a good amount of time. Got a good full group? Puller goes down steps and voila' 2 more gargs, down steps again, 2 MORE gargs(on right) That's 6 spawns all total. Need to run? NO problem go back thru torture room head straight to tower and jump left, your at zone. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>Garthin Trueknight<br>52 Pally<br>Brell Server<br>Member of Freedom Fighters<br>&quot;Better to try and fail, then to never try at all&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugarthintrueknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garthin Trueknight</A> at: 4/5/01 8:26:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugarthintrueknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garthin Trueknight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/5/01 8:04:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Oh and a few more things LOL. Go to treecity by bank and buy some invis potions, 16pp each to me a human pally cons indiff. Then go to mm castle and do a /w of zone. Then ask for camp check. If anyone is camping advisor or xicotl or cherissa, then kindly ask them if they need all the granite drops, same thing goes for maid/butler cooks camp. Then invis AND GO TO THEM. expecting high level farmers or a group leader to come get ya, is just not gonna happen unless the persons just died and are going back in. Take the initiative to get a good map(eqmaps.com) and go in. Afaid to lose your main? create a mule, invis him and go in and learn castle.<br><br>Garthin Trueknight<br>52 Pally<br>Brell Server<br>Member Freedom Fighters<br>&quot;But it conned BLUE!&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabazagaroth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abazagaroth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/18/01 11:16:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> At 40 you should have NO problem gettng melatite on your own, you just need to get to the clockworks, and look for the patterns. There are up to 8 clocks you can get without too much trouble by yourself, if you time them right, pull them right, etc. Also, it takes FOREVER to get KOS to them, I've probably killed 50+ since I went dubious and am still dubious. Exp and loot isn't bad either, just gotta know what you are doing, and where to pull so that you don't end up with more than two on you at once. If one breaks root and runs, just let it go. It won't aggro others unless you follow it, and it will head back without having gained much hp back, just wait and prepare to root or stun.<br><br>Abazagaroth<br> <p>C. David Kreger, Pennsylvania State University<br>Webmaster:<br><a href="http://www.humanevolution.f2s.com" target="_top">A Look at Modern Human Origins</a><br>Moderator:<br><a href="http://www3.cybercities.com/h/humanorigins/webring.html" target="_top">Paleoanthropology Web Resources Webring</a><br>Moderator:<br><a href="http://pub19.ezboard.com/balookatmodernhumanorigins" target="_top">Human Evolution Message Board</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthunderhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thunderhart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/01 11:05:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.guildmagic.com/pics/4482.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Silly question, perhaps, but where does one buy the platinum that you need to get enchanted?<br><br>I pretty much have everything else (melatite, Sands of Ro, Soil of Underfoot, etc.) just need to know where to get this.<br><br>Thanks, <p>Thunderhart<br>38th campaign Paladin of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uantonustbc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AntonusTBC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/01 11:36:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Platinum bars are sold at the local jewelry vendors.  You'll need to get them enchanted by an enchanter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthunderhart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thunderhart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/1/01 1:34:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2884.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.guildmagic.com/pics/4482.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armour of Ro Quest - Advice needed</span><hr size=1> Thanks very much! Happily, I have a few Enchanter friends. <p>Thunderhart<br>38th campaign Paladin of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showPrevMessage?topicID=2884.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showNextMessage?topicID=2884.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><